snippet: A study found that pregnant women who feared childbirth the most at 32 weeks gestation had an average labor 47 minutes longer than those who were less afraid.
abstract: A study found that pregnant women who feared childbirth the most at 32 weeks gestation had an average labor 47 minutes longer than those who were less afraid.
